National HealthCorp LP saidit has started adding 46 beds for its Greenwood Health CareCenter in Greenwood, S.C., and plans to add 10 beds to itsSpringfield Health Care Center in Springfield, Tenn.    The company said it has opened Colonial Hill RetirementApartments adjacent to its Colonial Hill Health Care Center inJohnson City, Tenn., and has completely remodeled NationalHealth Care Center in Lawrenceburg, Tenn.    It said it is acquiring the title to that center, which hadbeen owned by Lawrence County Lions Club and called LionsNursing Home.    National said the projects will cost a total of about3,500,000 dlrs. Reuter&#3;